The measures we recently rolled out will undoubtfully address a wide range of challenges and improve passenger experience at JKIA   with enhanced operational efficiency that guarantees travellers' safety and security.

Having received a lot of feedback from several quarters, especially on the security checks of inbound luggage, the team has set up dedicated screening rooms, to ensure our travelers’ privacy, this screening will only affect bags flagged by security scanners. The Advanced Passenger Information Systems as well as electronic Self-Clearance gates will facilitate faster immigration processing, addressing the alleged delays and long queues.
These measures are a boost to our tourism sector, especially those with transit visas, since they will be operating within a limited timeline. Coupled with the recent pronounced eTA exemptions for our African travellers, we can only expect a surge of both local and international tourists to Kenya in the coming days.
