Hola, Tana River County.
14 June 2025.

I Joined @Kenya_Ports Manager Medical Services Dr. Gome Lenga , Senior Communication Officer (CSI) @SerahTuva , KPA And County Government Of Tana River Medical Staff During A Free Medical Camp As Part Of KPA's Corporate Social Investment Program In Collaboration With The County Government.

At Least 1200 Residents Of Hola Town And It's Environ Benefited From Free Outpatient Care With Common Ailments Including Respiratory Infections, Abdominal Illnesses, And Hypertension, Eye Care, Cervical Cancer Screening, And General Consultancy.

Tana River County Provides Early Evacuation Route For Cargo Handled At Port Of Lamu Through Lamu - Garsen - Hola - Bura - Garissa Road Hence This Corporate Social Responsibility Is Aimed At Advancing Healthcare In Marginalized Areas Along The Transport Corridor. 

